			<div class="content">Adverbial conjunctions? Casual clauses? I'm totally lost on some of the words in that paragraph. Your excerpt  confused me a little, Hektor6766san  <img src="http://thejapanesepage.com/phpbb/images/smilies/sweatdrop.gif" alt=":sweatdrop:" title="Sweatdrop" />...but I think I get the gist of it.  I now remember why grammar lessons always gave me a pain the rear...<br /><br />Does that mean I was basically right though? As long as the &quot;because clause' is complete, the sentence is correct?  The following sentence with because doesn't start a noun clause, but just a regular sentence. <br /><br />Because I had a lot of money, I went to Las Vegas.<br /><br />I went to Las Vegas because I had a lot of money.<br /><br />These are both right...right?<br /><br />But a sentence like this:<br />&quot;Because I had a lot of money from my friends.&quot; isn't right because it is a sentence fragment. (Thanks Hyperworm, I had a brain fart there! <img src="http://thejapanesepage.com/phpbb/images/smilies/razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" /> ) <br /><br />Well, off to search for adverbial conjunctions and the like.</div>

			

